### Steps to reproduce

1. Use SliverPersistentHeaderDelegate which has TextField or TextFormField as child in SliverPersistentHeader inside CustomScrollView.
2. Set the floating of the SliverPersistentHeader to true.
3. Scroll down to hide the header.
4. Scroll up slightly to see the header.
5. Scrolling is initialized when the TextField in the header is clicked.

### Expected results

The scroll position should be maintained.

### Actual results

When the focus is moved by clicking on the TextField, the scroll position is initialized.

