Some observations:
* `CupertinoTextField` will load without any localizations provided to `WidgetsApp`, but will crash when doing something like opening the context menu because of those missing localizations. We should probably assert and document this in `CupertinoTextField`.
* `CupertinoTextField` currently "works" on all `App` variants without any changes.
* Removing the assert for material ancestors in `TextField` lets us use `TextField` in `CupertinoApp` and `WidgetsApp`.
* It looks like passing a `decoration` to `TextField` when used under `WidgetsApp` does not require it to have a material ancestor.

Looks like `CupertinoTextField` and `TextField` should be able to be used in any `App` context given that the proper localizations are defined. I'll work on verifying this further and making this change.

