I want to say that users will typically want the context menu to be axis-aligned, so we should fix this at the framework level rather than relying on a workaround. If anyone out there actually wants their context menu to be transformed along with the field, please leave a comment!

 > Only parts of the TextField respond to tap events on a rotated TextField.

This is probably because there are places in the text event handling where we are doing improper math when we should have just used getTransformTo. I've seen bugs like this before when we manually calculated the difference in offsets on the screen without considering the full details of each element's transformation matrix. I'll see if I notice anything suspicious but it might be kind of whack-a-mole to get this working properly.
